results.name: Decimal expansion of 2*sqrt(3)/(9*Pi).
comment: The ratio of the volume of a regular tetrahedron to the volume of the circumscribed sphere. (The MathWorld link shows that the circumradius for a tetrahedron with side length a is a*sqrt(6)/4.)
link: Jackson, Frank and Weisstein, Eric W., "Tetrahedron"
results.author: _Rick L. Shepherd_, Sep 30 2009
